Searching records - multi criteria

1. Let's search for records in the Catalog module (Catalog(Geol) tab)

Each text box in this view is a search field. You can type your text or pick from pre-filled lookup lists.

We are going to search for all the records in the "Coors Mineral Hall" location that are part of the Rock collection in the Earth Sciences department.


2. Click the icon on the right of the "Department" field

Whenever that icon is present, it means that the particular field has a pre-filled list of options that you can pick from.

3. Click "Earth Sciences"

Click "OK" to accept your choice.

4. Click the icon to the right of the "Collection" field
5. Click "Rocks"

Click "OK" to accept your choice.

6. Type "Coors Mineral Hall" in the "Location" field
7. Click the binocular icon on the top left to perform the search

This will search for all the terms in the selected fields at the same time.

8. The results of your search will display

We will go into detail in this view later. For now, notice what this window looks like.
